the divided
states of America.

01:31.992 --> 01:36.496 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Meanwhile, the president-elect
made more picks
of his own, announcing he will
nominate Iowa

01:36.530 --> 01:40.600 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Governor Terry Branstad as his
ambassador
to China.

01:40.634 --> 01:44.805 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Branstad is a Republican and the
longest-serving
governor of Iowa ever.

01:44.838 --> 01:49.576 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
He was one of the most prominent
establishment
Republicans to support Mr. Trump
in the election,

01:49.609 --> 01:54.348 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
and he has a longstanding
friendship with
the Chinese president, Xi
Jinping.

01:54.381 --> 01:58.919 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Another official announcement,
former wresting
executive Linda McMahon is Mr.
Trump's nominee

01:58.952 --> 02:01.888 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
to head the Small Business
Administration.

02:01.922 --> 02:06.159 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Also today, the Associated Press
and other
outlets reported retired Marine
General John

02:06.193 --> 02:09.262 align:left position:12.5%,start line:80% size:87.5%
Kelly is the choice for
secretary of homeland
security.

02:09.296 --> 02:11.131 align:left position:12.5%,start line:80% size:87.5%
DONALD TRUMP (R),
President-Elect: Great,
great general.

02:11.164 --> 02:15.202 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
LISA DESJARDINS: And multiple
outlets also
reported Oklahoma Attorney
General Scott Pruitt

02:15.235 --> 02:19.406 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
as Mr. Trump's pick to lead the
Environmental
Protection Agency.

02:19.439 --> 02:22.609 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Pruitt is known for opposing EPA
climate change
regulations.

02:22.642 --> 02:25.078 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
DONALD TRUMP: Mad Dog Mattis.

02:25.112 --> 02:29.983 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
LISA DESJARDINS: All this after
the incoming
commander in chief officially
introduced retired

02:30.017 --> 02:35.489 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Marine General James Mattis as
his selection
for secretary of defense at a
rally last night

02:35.522 --> 02:37.758 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
in Fayetteville, North Carolina.

02:37.791 --> 02:41.228 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Mattis would need a waiver from
Congress to
accept the position because he's
been out

02:41.261 --> 02:43.196 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
of the service less than seven
years.

02:43.230 --> 02:44.297 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
DONALD TRUMP: What a great guy.

02:44.331 --> 02:45.298 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
He's going to be incredible.

02:45.332 --> 02:46.299 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
