02:46.333 --> 02:47.834 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
He's going to get that.

02:47.868 --> 02:53.640 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Oh, if he didn't get that
waiver, there would
be a lot of angry people.

02:53.673 --> 02:58.345 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
LISA DESJARDINS: The stop in
North Carolina
is part of a clear ramp-up of
travel for Mr.

02:58.378 --> 03:00.113 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
Trump.

03:00.147 --> 03:02.716 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
Tomorrow, he will be in
Columbus, Ohio, to
meet with responders to the Ohio
State campus

03:02.749 --> 03:06.686 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
attack last week, then a thank
you rally in
Des Moines, Iowa.

03:06.720 --> 03:10.757 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Friday, the stops are Baton
Rouge, Louisiana,
to support the Republican Senate
candidate

03:10.791 --> 03:15.362 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
in a runoff, and another thank
you rally in
Grand Rapids, Michigan.

03:15.395 --> 03:19.132 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
President-elect Trump said today
he thinks
his biggest remaining pick,
secretary of state,

03:19.166 --> 03:20.901 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
