03:20.934 --> 03:24.004 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
This morning, he also told "The
Today Show"
he's getting advice from his
predecessor.

03:24.037 --> 03:25.705 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
DONALD TRUMP: I will say this.

03:25.739 --> 03:28.875 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
I have now gotten to know
President Obama.

03:28.909 --> 03:30.644 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
I really like him.

03:30.677 --> 03:37.250 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
We obviously very much disagree
on certain
policy and certain things, but I
really like

03:37.284 --> 03:38.985 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
him as a person.

03:39.019 --> 03:42.489 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
LISA DESJARDINS: And, today, Mr.
Trump met
with the president's first chief
of staff,

03:42.522 --> 03:47.694 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Chicago Mayor Rahm Emanuel, who
said he argued
for so-called dreamers,
undocumented Americans

03:47.727 --> 03:49.396 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
brought here as children.

03:49.429 --> 03:51.531 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
For the "PBS NewsHour," I'm Lisa
Desjardins.

03:51.565 --> 03:56.436 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: In the day's
other news: A
Charleston, South Carolina, jury
heard opening

03:56.470 --> 04:02.642 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
statements in the trial of
Dylann Roof, the
man charged with murdering nine
black churchgoers.

04:02.676 --> 04:04.511 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
It happened in June 2015.

04:04.544 --> 04:09.816 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Today, a federal prosecutor
declared Roof
had a cold and hateful heart.

04:09.850 --> 04:14.187 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
The defense conceded Roof's
guilt, and focused
on preventing a death sentence.

04:14.221 --> 04:19.926 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Later, a survivor broke down as
she testified
about seeing her son die in the
gunfire.

04:19.960 --> 04:23.163 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
HARI SREENIVASAN: Authorities in
Tennessee
have charged two juveniles with
setting a

04:23.196 --> 04:27.134 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
deadly wildfire that roared
through the Great
Smoky Mountains two weeks ago.

04:27.167 --> 04:32.572 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Fourteen people died and more
than 1,700 buildings
were damaged or destroyed as
high winds blew

04:32.606 --> 04:35.175 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
the flames into the Gatlinburg
area.

04:35.208 --> 04:38.912 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Prosecutors left open the
possibility that
others could be charged as well.

04:38.945 --> 04:43.183 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: Recovery efforts
came to an
end today at the scene of the
deadly warehouse

04:43.216 --> 04:45.385 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
fire in Oakland, California.

04:45.418 --> 04:49.289 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
The death toll from the weekend
tragedy stands
at 36.

04:49.322 --> 04:53.793 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Investigators have turned their
attention
to a refrigerator as a possible
cause.

04:53.827 --> 04:58.331 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
The fast-moving fire ripped
through the warehouse,
where a dance party was under
way.

04:58.365 --> 05:03.136 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
HARI SREENIVASAN: In Indonesia,
the earth
shook before dawn today,
knocking down buildings,

05:03.170 --> 05:05.505 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
and sending terrified people
into the streets.

05:05.539 --> 05:10.810 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
At least 97 were killed, with
hundreds more
injured.

05:10.844 --> 05:17.384 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
It was a picture of desperation,
rescue crews
using bare hands to dig through
twisted wreckage,

05:17.417 --> 05:19.920 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
while excavators removed heavier
debris.

05:19.953 --> 05:24.925 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
MAN (through translator): We
estimate the
number of casualties will
continue to rise,

05:24.958 --> 05:28.528 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
as some of the residents are
still likely
under the rubble of the
buildings.

05:28.562 --> 05:30.797 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
The search-and-rescue operation
is still under
way.

05:30.830 --> 05:36.036 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
HARI SREENIVASAN: The quake hit
shortly after
5:00 a.m., registered 6.5, and
was centered

05:36.069 --> 05:39.606 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
around the northern tip of Aceh
province on
Sumatra Island.

05:39.639 --> 05:42.309 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
But it was too shallow to
trigger a tsunami.

05:42.342 --> 05:48.215 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
Still, it was all too
reminiscent of the far
more powerful quake and tsunami
that devastated

05:48.248 --> 05:54.421 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
the same region in 2004, killing
more than
100,000 people in Aceh alone.

05:54.454 --> 05:58.191 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
That disaster prompted efforts
to improve
warnings and readiness.

05:58.225 --> 06:02.963 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
But Kanupriya Kapoor with
Reuters said the
quake-prone country still has a
long way to

06:02.996 --> 06:03.964 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
go.

06:03.997 --> 06:05.765 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
She spoke to us via Skype from
Jakarta.

06:05.799 --> 06:09.269 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
KANUPRIYA KAPOOR, Reuters: If I
were to speak
to the readiness of these
communities, the

06:09.302 --> 06:14.641 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
preparedness to deal with a
quake, I wouldn't
be surprised if they aren't as
prepared, if,

06:14.674 --> 06:20.880 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
you know, structures in this
area, you know,
were clearly not built to
withstand even a

06:20.914 --> 06:22.716 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
6.5-magnitude earthquake.

06:22.749 --> 06:28.255 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
HARI SREENIVASAN: Indonesia's
disaster agency
estimates some 245 buildings,
including 14

06:28.288 --> 06:33.460 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
mosques, were either seriously
damaged or
destroyed in today's quake,
leaving thousands

06:33.493 --> 06:35.295 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
of people homeless.

06:35.328 --> 06:40.233 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
The Indonesian government has
officially declared
a two-week state of emergency in
Aceh.

06:40.267 --> 06:45.171 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: In the mountains
of Northern
Pakistan, no one survived an
airplane crash

06:45.205 --> 06:46.706 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
today.

06:46.740 --> 06:51.077 align:left position:12.5%,start line:80% size:87.5%
The head of Pakistan
International Airlines
says 48 people were on board.

06:51.111 --> 06:56.316 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Witnesses said the plane burst
into flames
and went down about 50 miles
outside Islamabad.

06:56.349 --> 07:03.957 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Junaid Jamshed, a well-known
Pakistani-singer-turned-evangeli
cal-Muslim-cleric,
was among those who perished.

07:03.990 --> 07:06.393 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
The cause of the crash is under
investigation.

07:06.426 --> 07:11.131 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
HARI SREENIVASAN: The U.S. and
five other
Western nations are calling for
a new cease-fire

07:11.164 --> 07:14.601 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
in Aleppo, Syria, in a bid to
get civilians
out.

07:14.634 --> 07:18.805 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
They also accused Russia today
of blocking
efforts to end the bloodshed.

07:18.838 --> 07:22.309 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Meanwhile, Syrian government
troops and their
allies pushed deeper into
Eastern Aleppo.

07:22.342 --> 07:27.947 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
They now control about 75
percent of what
was the rebel-held area of the
city.

07:27.981 --> 07:33.153 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: Back in this
country, a bipartisan
bill to speed federal drug
approvals and bolster

07:33.186 --> 07:36.823 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
research overwhelmingly passed
the Senate
today.

07:36.856 --> 07:40.260 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
President Obama promised to sign
the $6 billion
measure.

07:40.293 --> 07:46.399 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
It includes funding for Vice
President Biden's
Moonshot effort to find a cure
for cancer

07:46.433 --> 07:49.235 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
and for a stepped-up campaign to
fight opioid
abuse.

07:49.269 --> 07:53.073 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
HARI SREENIVASAN: Senators also
paid tribute
today to Vice President Biden.

07:53.106 --> 07:56.343 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
He served there for 36 years
representing
Delaware.

07:56.376 --> 08:00.947 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
He was back today in his
official role as
president of the Senate,
listening as lawmakers

08:00.980 --> 08:04.217 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
