Challenge.

22:41.694 --> 22:46.131 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
It's a competition in which
students from
around the world submitted
videos explaining

22:46.165 --> 22:50.269 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
some very tough scientific
concepts, probably
better than I am right now.

22:50.302 --> 22:54.640 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
Deanna chose antibiotic
resistance in bacteria.

22:54.673 --> 22:59.712 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
And Antonella discussed quantum
entanglement
-- quantum entanglement, not bad
for a high

22:59.745 --> 23:00.713 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
schooler.

23:00.746 --> 23:02.982 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
So, what does the award mean to
her?

23:03.015 --> 23:05.684 align:left position:12.5%,start line:80% size:87.5%
Fewer entanglements with
scholarships and
student loans.

23:05.718 --> 23:07.519 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
Let's listen.

23:07.553 --> 23:08.988 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
ANTONELLA MASINI, Breakthrough
Junior Challenge
Winner: I have a little
economical problems

23:09.021 --> 23:10.756 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
at home.

23:10.789 --> 23:15.394 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
And now with this prize, I can
choose any
school that I want, any college
that I want.

23:15.427 --> 23:16.528 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
And it's unbelievable.

23:16.562 --> 23:19.865 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
I'm really grateful -- grateful
for this opportunity.

23:19.898 --> 23:21.367 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
And will never forget it.

23:21.400 --> 23:23.902 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
MILES O'BRIEN: And I have a
feeling, Hari,
we won't forget her either.

23:23.936 --> 23:28.540 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
HARI SREENIVASAN: Miles, we were
such slackers
compared to just those two kids,
much less

23:28.574 --> 23:30.075 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
probably all the kids that were
nominated
there.

23:30.109 --> 23:31.277 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
MILES O'BRIEN: It's why we're
here.

23:31.310 --> 23:32.278 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
(LAUGHTER)

23:32.311 --> 23:33.512 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
HARI SREENIVASAN: All right.

23:33.545 --> 23:36.181 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Thank you, Miles O'Brien,
joining us from
Boston tonight.

23:36.215 --> 23:47.893 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: Stay with us.

23:47.926 --> 23:54.633 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Coming up on the "NewsHour": the
art of the
Qur'an, a new exhibit featuring
