needed for him
to stay.

28:37.749 --> 28:41.520 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
But he said, "But you have a job
to do."

28:41.553 --> 28:49.328 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
And he -- that one phrase made
me pull myself
together and do my job.

28:49.361 --> 28:52.030 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
My peers came to my defense.

28:52.064 --> 28:58.370 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
And the commissioner, Peter
Ueberroth, who
was in his first week in office,
the next

28:58.403 --> 29:07.846 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
day passed an edict: All
credentialed -- properly
credentialed reporters, no
matter gender,

29:07.879 --> 29:14.820 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
race, religion, whatever planet
they came
from, get access in Major League
Baseball.

29:14.853 --> 29:18.624 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
He couldn't believe that it
really hadn't
happened before.

29:18.657 --> 29:22.728 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
But on his watch, from that day
forward, it
was going to happen.

29:22.761 --> 29:28.667 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: And you were not
deterred,
and you have kept on ever since
then.

29:28.700 --> 29:31.603 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
Has it been harder, though, as
an African-American?

29:31.637 --> 29:36.174 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Or have you just not looked back
and thought
about that since then?

29:36.208 --> 29:39.344 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
CLAIRE SMITH: It was no contest.

29:39.378 --> 29:42.314 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
It was harder because of gender
than race.

29:42.347 --> 29:54.393 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
I have always said that, because
a sport had
-- at that time had a much
larger representation

29:54.426 --> 30:02.901 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
of African-Americans in uniform,
and still
